00:00:54,455 --> 00:00:58,791
narrator: exercise bikes can provide a great cardio workout.            

4
00:00:58,793 --> 00:01:00,058
their tension settings      

5
00:01:00,060 --> 00:01:04,196
are equivalent to the gears on a road bike.         

6
00:01:04,198 --> 00:01:07,532
cyclists can adjust the tension to control the intensity     

7
00:01:07,534 --> 00:01:10,836
of their workout, all while staying in one place.             

8
00:01:15,143 --> 00:01:19,277
riding an exercise bike can help burn calories,     

9
00:01:19,279 --> 00:01:22,415
increase strength, and reach fitness goals.     

10
00:01:24,351 --> 00:01:27,285
they start by making the bike frame,         

11
00:01:27,287 --> 00:01:29,822
which includes the handlebars, saddle post,           

12
00:01:29,824 --> 00:01:32,157
and flywheel housing.      

13
00:01:32,159 --> 00:01:36,962
an employee places all the parts in a welding fixture.      

14
00:01:36,964 --> 00:01:39,699
the welding system is computerized.         

15
00:01:39,701 --> 00:01:42,634
the fixture moves the parts into position          

16
00:01:42,636 --> 00:01:46,205
and a robot accurately     
welds the joints of the frame.  

17
00:01:48,509 --> 00:01:53,045
it takes 20 welds to link all the parts of the bike frame.             

18
00:01:53,047 --> 00:01:56,648
at the next station, a machine shapes the handlebars      

19
00:01:56,650 --> 00:01:58,584
and saddle post to the correct profile.     

20
00:02:02,390 --> 00:02:05,658
then, a worker polishes the welds with a wire brush.   

21
00:02:08,396 --> 00:02:12,130
next, they apply a black plastic finish to the metal.       

22
00:02:12,132 --> 00:02:15,201
this process is called powder coating.         

23
00:02:15,203 --> 00:02:18,537
an employee applies a metallic decal of the company name    

24
00:02:18,539 --> 00:02:20,072
to the powder-coated frame.   

25
00:02:23,444 --> 00:02:26,278
he inserts the bearing for the pedal crank axle     

26
00:02:26,280 --> 00:02:28,614
and gently taps it into place with a hammer.          

27
00:02:30,284 --> 00:02:32,818
he attaches a circuit board to the base.           

28
00:02:32,820 --> 00:02:36,222
it will control the resistance of the flywheel.         

29
00:02:36,224 --> 00:02:38,624
he threads the wiring through the hollow frame     

30
00:02:38,626 --> 00:02:40,326
and out the handlebar post.   

31
00:02:43,497 --> 00:02:46,498
he drills holes in the saddle-bar tubing,    

32
00:02:46,500 --> 00:02:49,735
then, he installs the post and adjustable locking screw.  

33
00:02:52,373 --> 00:02:56,441
he installs a temporary clamping lever on the flywheel framework,           

34
00:02:56,443 --> 00:02:59,078
which will be used to tension the transmission build.     

35
00:03:03,251 --> 00:03:05,117
he installs the bike saddle.   

36
00:03:07,455 --> 00:03:11,123
then, he uses a hydraulic system to press an axle and bearing   

37
00:03:11,125 --> 00:03:12,825
into the center of the flywheel.            

38
00:03:18,532 --> 00:03:21,133
he places a product-name decal on the flywheel.         

39
00:03:23,003 --> 00:03:27,005
the cast-iron flywheel is the heart of the bike.    

40
00:03:27,007 --> 00:03:30,476
at about 40 pounds, it's heavy enough to stabilize the bike   

41
00:03:30,478 --> 00:03:32,044
during the stationary ride.   

42
00:03:36,217 --> 00:03:40,018
he loops the transmission belt around the flywheel axle,    

43
00:03:40,020 --> 00:03:42,288
then mounts the flywheel to the framework.        

44
00:03:44,491 --> 00:03:48,894
he installs magnetic brakes and              
wires them to a bike computer.  

45
00:03:48,896 --> 00:03:51,363
the brakes allow the rider to control the resistance    

46
00:03:51,365 --> 00:03:52,631
during the ride.         

47
00:03:55,436 --> 00:03:58,037
he connects the pulley disk to the front of the bike.    

48
00:04:01,441 --> 00:04:03,976
then, he loops the other end of the transmission belt     

49
00:04:03,978 --> 00:04:05,077
around the pulley disk.     

50
00:04:06,847 --> 00:04:10,182
he uses a clamping lever to pull the belt tight.     

51
00:04:10,184 --> 00:04:12,117
he strums it and measures the sound      

52
00:04:12,119 --> 00:04:13,753
to confirm the tension is right.            

53
00:04:15,389 --> 00:04:17,455
the next worker removes the clamp        

54
00:04:17,457 --> 00:04:21,126
and places the bike in a test station.        

55
00:04:21,128 --> 00:04:24,330
it spins the flywheel and applies resistance.     

56
00:04:24,332 --> 00:04:26,665
a computer analyzes the bike's performance.     

57
00:04:28,535 --> 00:04:30,803
another employee wires the switches        

58
00:04:30,805 --> 00:04:33,038
for increasing and decreasing resistance.    

59
00:04:34,808 --> 00:04:37,676
she tucks the wiring inside the handlebars.      

60
00:04:37,678 --> 00:04:40,011
she attaches switches to the outside          

61
00:04:40,013 --> 00:04:41,714
for easy access during the ride.         

62
00:04:45,686 --> 00:04:48,888
she folds the lower half of the resistance wiring up   

63
00:04:48,890 --> 00:04:52,057
and installs the wiring sleeve in between the handlebars.    

64
00:04:54,295 --> 00:04:57,029
she screws the bracket to the handlebar housing,    

65
00:04:57,031 --> 00:04:59,765
then, she connects the wires to the ride computer       

66
00:04:59,767 --> 00:05:01,567
and attaches it to the bracket.            

67
00:05:03,503 --> 00:05:04,770
she opens the computer      

68
00:05:04,772 --> 00:05:08,707
and plugs the main power cable into the back.          

69
00:05:08,709 --> 00:05:12,577
then, she reinstalls the computer's back panel.    

70
00:05:12,579 --> 00:05:14,547
this completes the handlebar assembly.     

71
00:05:16,450 --> 00:05:19,051
the next worker encases the transmission belt      

72
00:05:19,053 --> 00:05:21,320
and electrical parts in a plastic housing.      

73
00:05:24,658 --> 00:05:26,692
he attaches the pedals to the axle.           

74
00:05:28,529 --> 00:05:30,929
then, he places plastic caps on the ends     

75
00:05:30,931 --> 00:05:32,698
and hammers them into place.   

76
00:05:35,803 --> 00:05:39,038
he packages the bike and    
handlebar assembly separately.  

77
00:05:43,410 --> 00:05:47,680
this exercise bike is now ready to ride.      

78
00:05:47,682 --> 00:05:50,816
it may be stationary,      
but, when it comes to fitness,  

79
00:05:50,818 --> 00:05:53,819
this bike should help riders go the distance.     

