00:16:51,611 --> 00:16:54,211
artisans are using slate to create everyday items,    

252
00:16:54,213 --> 00:16:56,747
including tableware, address plaques,         

253
00:16:56,749 --> 00:16:58,517
and garden accessories.     

254
00:17:02,623 --> 00:17:05,957
these cornish slate products use              
traditional building materials  

255
00:17:05,959 --> 00:17:07,559
in nontraditional ways.     

256
00:17:09,896 --> 00:17:11,363
in cornwall,           

257
00:17:11,365 --> 00:17:13,298
they have been mining slate for hundreds of years.      

258
00:17:16,369 --> 00:17:18,503
some of the craftsman's slate is old roof           

259
00:17:18,505 --> 00:17:22,173
or floor tile retrieved from the demolition sites.    

260
00:17:22,175 --> 00:17:26,243
other projects require new slate, fresh from the quarry.  

261
00:17:26,245 --> 00:17:27,512
the craftsman selects      

262
00:17:27,514 --> 00:17:29,848
and older piece from a cheese board.       

263
00:17:29,850 --> 00:17:33,651
he evaluates the color, as well as the thickness and shape.   

264
00:17:33,653 --> 00:17:36,788
older slate is weathered and has more colors running through it.               

265
00:17:41,928 --> 00:17:44,796
he scrapes the loose slate off the surface,         

266
00:17:44,798 --> 00:17:46,264
working carefully to avoid    

267
00:17:46,266 --> 00:17:48,900
fracturing the stone's thin layers.           

268
00:17:51,338 --> 00:17:52,804
he sweeps off the scrapings.   

269
00:17:55,408 --> 00:17:59,344
he scrubs the slate tile with a chemical cleaning solution   

270
00:17:59,346 --> 00:18:01,046
and rinses off the residue.   

271
00:18:03,283 --> 00:18:06,217
the slate dries in minutes.   

272
00:18:06,219 --> 00:18:10,288
as the water evaporates,    
the color changes dramatically  

273
00:18:10,290 --> 00:18:12,791
from dark gray to light gray with a bluish hue.        

274
00:18:15,429 --> 00:18:17,228
he measures the slate for cutting           

275
00:18:17,230 --> 00:18:20,765
and scores it lightly with a sharp tool.        

276
00:18:20,767 --> 00:18:22,500
he places a template for the handle          

277
00:18:22,502 --> 00:18:24,936
within the scored boundaries and marks it for drilling.    

278
00:18:29,242 --> 00:18:32,710
then, he cuts the slate with a slate guillotine.     

279
00:18:32,712 --> 00:18:35,513
it's a double-bladed tool similar to a paper cutter.    

280
00:18:37,918 --> 00:18:39,884
he leaves a margin for trimming.            

281
00:18:44,925 --> 00:18:46,191
he breaks off the margin     

282
00:18:46,193 --> 00:18:49,794
by tapping it with a special slater's tool   

283
00:18:49,796 --> 00:18:52,364
and checks the edges, to confirm that they're neat.  

284
00:18:54,333 --> 00:18:59,070
then, he redefines the markings for the handle holds.      

285
00:18:59,072 --> 00:19:01,339
the craftsman drills holes through the slate        

286
00:19:01,341 --> 00:19:04,809
for the handles.         

287
00:19:04,811 --> 00:19:06,544
then, he changes the drill bit  

288
00:19:06,546 --> 00:19:09,213
to cut a sloped profile into the holes.         

289
00:19:09,215 --> 00:19:12,684
this will allow the screws to sit flush against the slate.             

290
00:19:16,556 --> 00:19:19,357
he brushes the edges, to get rid of loose chips,    

291
00:19:19,359 --> 00:19:21,660
and refines the ends with a razor blade.       

292
00:19:24,297 --> 00:19:26,865
the craftsman washes the slate one more time.          

293
00:19:29,235 --> 00:19:34,105
the glues four small silicone knobs onto the base.       

294
00:19:34,107 --> 00:19:35,973
the knobs act as legs,      

295
00:19:35,975 --> 00:19:40,178
so the cheese plate can be set on any surface.    

296
00:19:40,180 --> 00:19:44,248
he applies two coats of     
food-safe sealer to the slate.  

297
00:19:44,250 --> 00:19:47,318
each coat takes a day to dry.  

298
00:19:47,320 --> 00:19:49,888
then, he installs the stainless-steel handles.   

299
00:19:55,796 --> 00:19:58,830
this slate cheese board is now ready to hold a few snacks.   

300
00:20:03,670 --> 00:20:06,271
from an old roof tile to a nice piece of tableware.  

301
00:20:06,273 --> 00:20:07,939
it's quite a transformation.   

302
00:20:15,549 --> 00:20:17,481
next, the craftsman slices    

303
00:20:17,483 --> 00:20:19,617
a block of new slate with a wet saw.         

304
00:20:21,755 --> 00:20:24,355
new slate comes in thicker chunks.        

305
00:20:24,357 --> 00:20:26,124
it can be used to make signage.            

306
00:20:31,364 --> 00:20:34,565
he uses eight different grades of diamond abrasive pads     

307
00:20:34,567 --> 00:20:37,802
to polish the surface until it's completely flat.   

308
00:20:39,573 --> 00:20:42,106
then, he uses a computerized graphic cutter          

309
00:20:42,108 --> 00:20:43,641
to make a stencil out of vinyl.             

310
00:20:46,847 --> 00:20:48,980
he places the stencil over the slate          

311
00:20:48,982 --> 00:20:51,149
and sandblasts it with a special compound.     

312
00:20:54,521 --> 00:20:58,523
the process creates rough grooves in the slate.      

313
00:20:58,525 --> 00:21:01,493
the grooves will allow paint to adhere to the stone.  

314
00:21:04,397 --> 00:21:06,463
another employee uses the stencil         

315
00:21:06,465 --> 00:21:09,134
to apply paint to the slate.   

316
00:21:09,136 --> 00:21:11,069
she allows each coat of the paint to dry       

317
00:21:11,071 --> 00:21:12,637
before brushing on the next.   

318
00:21:16,276 --> 00:21:19,677
she applies four coats in total.             

319
00:21:19,679 --> 00:21:22,247
when she's finished, she peels off the vinyl.     

320
00:21:26,353 --> 00:21:30,755
this custom slate sign is ready of face the street.   

321
00:21:30,757 --> 00:21:34,826
it takes four days to craft, seal, and paint the sign.    

322
00:21:34,828 --> 00:21:36,294
now that it's complete,     

323
00:21:36,296 --> 00:21:39,130
the sign is sure to make a rock-solid impression.     

